Question 2

(a) List the system calls required for file creation, writing, reading, and closing.

The system calls required are:

open()
write()
read()
close()

These system calls are used to create or open a file, write data into the file, read data from the file, and finally close the file after completing the operations.

(b) Explain the purpose of any two file management system calls.

open()
The open() system call opens an existing file or creates a new file if it does not exist. It returns a file descriptor, which is used by other system calls to access the file.

write()
The write() system call writes data from the program into the specified file. It stores the information permanently in secondary storage and returns the number of bytes written successfully.

